      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Planning Node Types - Complete Proposal\n\nThis task graph now contains the **approved, ready-to-implement** definitions for the first wave of planning node types.\n\n**Goal achieved**: Every node type has a clear purpose, canonical data shape, relationship rules, and architecture constraints.\n\nAll planning nodes are static-first, fragment-safe, graph-authoritative (dictionary demoted), and ready for Codex execution prompts.\n\n**Next**: schema files, prompt templates, and dictionary registration (when you say go).",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
