    {
      "id": "nodeset-arch-node-vs-edge",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Node Type vs Edge Type",
      "position": {
        "x": 860,
        "y": -40
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "#8e24aa",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "flow",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        {
          "key": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "type": "flow"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "key": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "type": "content"
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Node Type vs Edge Type\n\n**Decision**: Dependency is **primarily an edge type** (fast, lightweight, already native to Twilite graphs). A Dependency **node** is allowed only when extra data/rationale/status is required.\n\n**Why**: Keeps graphs readable. Simple ordering = edge. Rich dependencies = node + edges.\n\n**Impact**: Constraint and Acceptance Criteria can also use edge metadata for lightweight cases; full nodes only when lifecycle is needed.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
